:: Title [Intro] {"position":"500,200","size":"100,100"}
<div class="title-hero">
# Introduction to Soldering
{
<p class="subtitle">A hands-on guide to soldering electronics.</p>
<p class="presenter">👋 Hi, I'm Monty DeGauven</p>
}
</div>
### Who am I?
I am a //mostly// normal dude who likes making things. I am not an electronics expert, a soldering genius, or someone who has every answer. I am a curious maker with a little experience, a lot of enthusiasm, and a belief that sometimes the right introduction can spark a lifelong interest.

I got my own start in a class a lot like this one, back when I was in an after school program at the Boys and Girls Club. They gave us a kit, a soldering iron, and a brief warning about not burning ourselves. It was the 90s, so that was apparently enough.

That experience stayed with me. It turned into years of tinkering, experimenting, learning, and making things. Maybe this class becomes that kind of spark for you too. If it does, Eugene Maker Space is the right place to keep experimenting, tinkering, and building.

